The `GET /v1/media` endpoint is handled by `App\Http\Controllers\Api\V1\MediaController@index`. This method returns a collection of `MediaResource` objects, which are paginated using Laravel's built-in paginator (defaulting to 20 items per page).

When a Laravel `JsonResource` collection wraps a paginated result, the response includes a `data` key containing the array of resources, along with `links` and `meta` keys for pagination information.

The `MediaResource` transforms each media item into an object with the following fields:
- `id`: The unique identifier of the media item.
- `name`: The name of the media.
- `url`: The full URL to the media file.
- `thumb_url`: The full URL to the thumbnail version of the media.

The response object for a successful `200 OK` request follows the standard Laravel paginated resource structure.

